    <!-- Color Theory Keys -->
    <string name="color_intro">The palette is your main tool for creating style. Colors affect psychological perception: warm (red, yellow) evoke energy and passion, cold (blue, green) act soothingly and symbolize stability. Choosing a color determines not only your look but also your mood.</string>
    <string name="color_essence">Each color has three characteristics: hue (name of the color), saturation (brightness or mutedness), and temperature (warm or cold). Knowing your color type (Winter, Spring, Summer, Autumn), you can choose ideal base colors that emphasize your natural beauty.</string>
    <string name="color_combos">Ideal combinations can be created using the Itten color wheel. Basic schemes: monochrome (shades of one color), analogous (colors next to each other), complementary (opposite colors for strong contrast), and triadic (three equidistant colors).</string>
    <string name="color_mixing" formatted="false">The main rule: use no more than three main colors in one look. The 60-30-10 formula works best: 60% — base color (e.g., suit), 30% — secondary (shirt), 10% — accent (tie, bag, shoes, or scarf).</string>

